allure serve target/allure-results
What this command does:
Builds the HTML report
Starts a temporary local server
Automatically opens your browser
Displays the full Allure dashboard
You’ll see:
	Test list
	Steps
	Attachments
	Screenshots
	Videos
	Logs
	Categories
	Suites
	Timeline

full interactive UI.

setup .bat command file in the project root(where pom.xml located)
add these commands in notepad and save file as a .bat file:
@echo off
echo Generating Allure report...
allure serve target/allure-results
pause



run allure report via server(not recommended)
generate a static HTML report only used via server. running this on local machine and java scripts will be blocked and no data is produced. 
allure generate target/allure-results --clean -o allure-report

then open index.html from your project folder...
allure-report/index.html

run on a server using commands (power shell):

cd allure-report
python -m http.server 8080

open using:
http://localhost:8080


Allure’s HTML uses JavaScript to load:
*.json
*.txt
*.png
*.webm

Browsers block this when opened from file:///.
So the UI loads, but the data never loads → “Loading…”







